<LegalPage eyebrow="About" heading="Mir Kash" lede="A beautiful bag shouldn&rsquo;t cost the earth. Or anything on it.">
  <p>Mir Kash was built around a simple belief &mdash; that wanting something beautiful and wanting a kinder world are not in conflict.</p>
  <p>Every bag is made from plant-based or synthetic vegan leathers: materials developed from fruit industry waste, not animal skin. The result feels like leather, wears like leather, and leaves nothing behind that shouldn&rsquo;t be there.</p>
  <p>We design for women who think about what they buy. Not in an anxious way. In a quiet, certain way. They&rsquo;ve stopped apologising for having taste, and they&rsquo;ve stopped pretending not to care about what goes into the things they own.</p>

  <h2>Your wardrobe doesn&rsquo;t have to choose</h2>
  <p>Choosing vegan shouldn&rsquo;t mean settling for a wardrobe that looks like a compromise. It should mean the opposite &mdash; every piece reflecting both your taste and your values, without one undermining the other. A Mir Kash bag should be the thing people ask about.</p>

  <h2>How we make things</h2>
  <p>Slowly. We go through long testing and trialling periods until the texture, the structure, and the weight feel exactly right. We&rsquo;d rather take longer and get it right.</p>

  <h2>The founder</h2>
  <p>Rajul Daga started Mir Kash because she couldn&rsquo;t find a bag she loved that she could also feel good about. The brand is an extension of that.</p>

  <h2>Three things we&rsquo;ll never do</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Use animal products.</li>
    <li>Rush a product.</li>
    <li>Pretend sustainability is a selling point rather than a baseline.</li>
  </ul>
</LegalPage>
